== Roasted Carrots ==

Adjust rack to top position and preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{9%ounce} on a diagonal into ½-inch-thick pieces. Halve, peel, and mince @shallot{1}. Roughly chop @walnuts{½%ounce}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @cinnamon{1%tsp} and @smoked paprika{1%tsp}.

Toss carrots on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @cooking oil{5%tsp}, half the cinnamon-paprika blend (you'll use more later), @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

== Walnut-Raisin Couscous ==

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add @Israeli couscous{2.5%ounce}, @golden raisins{1%ounce}, and half the shallot; cook, stirring, until couscous is lightly toasted and raisins and shallot are softened, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Add @chicken stock concentrate{1} and ¾ cup water; bring to a boil, then reduce to a low simmer and cover. Cook until couscous is tender, ~{6-8%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Chicken ==

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with paper towels and season all over with @garlic powder{1%tsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{5-7%minutes} per side. 

> TIP: If chicken is on the thicker side, reduce heat to medium; cover and cook for 2-3 minutes more per side.

Transfer to a #cutting board{} to rest. Reserve pan.

> Swap in pork or beef for chicken; cook pork until cooked through, 3-5 minutes per side, or cook beef to desired doneness, 4-7 minutes per side.

== Cranberry Pan Sauce ==

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in same pan over medium-high heat. Add remaining shallot, a pinch of @salt{}, and @pepper{}; cook, stirring occasionally, until fragrant and softened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in ½ cup water, @cranberry jam{1}, remaining @chicken stock concentrate{1}, remaining cinnamon-paprika blend, a pinch of @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until sauce begins to thicken, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Remove from heat and stir in @butter{1%tbsp} until melted. Taste and season with salt and pepper.

== To Serve ==

Stir walnuts into pot with couscous and season with salt and pepper to taste.

Slice chicken crosswise.

Divide chicken, couscous, and carrots between plates. Spoon sauce over chicken and serve.

> Slice chicken against the grain.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.